{"questionId":"9672","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Osaka Tigers basketball team play in a multilevel stadium.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e6cf518be54261b1431827ad0a7259ced8b4efde.png\"></p>\n<p>The most expensive tickets are in the first row. The ticket price, in Yen (¥), for each row forms&nbsp;an arithmetic sequence. Prices for the first three rows are shown in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/479626ab3d4429a69d498295e8f31a641d928463.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of the common difference, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span> =) − 250&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9672","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the value of the common difference, d","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}